reviews.review_text:
What's wrong with the PA? Hi GD Fans,   wow,  after looking for a upgrade to this show it seems to be in the crap bag from the beginning; every source sounds like crap.  The best source for a FM SBD is the latest and it's mono? It seems the best source is only a set one recording on master cassette by Andrew F. 20 feet from the stage; so we are picking up sound from the stage which is all the difference in fidelity.  

Another strange aspect is: after reading some reviews it seems that this show was a hot one , 105 degrees which could have plagued  the PA. However, Healy was using the gates/compression on the drums and you can hear it clamping down on the percussive dynamics.  You would think with Timothy Leary and Bear in attendence a priority would be placed on the PA sound?  I think it's a great show worthy of somebody getting into the vault for a better copy.  Perhaps, a candidate for a XM Sirius radio show?  It seems the GD always bring out the goods on Ky. Derby Day.

Sound "However, Healy was using the gates/compression on the drums and you can hear it clamping down on the percussive dynamics. You would think with Timothy Leary and Bear in attendence a priority would be placed on the PA sound? I think it's a great show worthy of somebody getting into the vault for a better copy."

How could they fix the sound/vault copy if Healy mixed it for the PA and thus master tapes. Quit complaining and enjoy what we have. 

I was there and was talking to Leary during drums on 5/6 - he really enjoyed the mix. Met Bear too after the show in Venice on 5/5. He wished there was something closer to a line array PA system for the flat Carson soccer field. He said it would have sounded better and better farther away. 

Regardless, this show sounded great up close! 5-6 was even better and better sounding.
